Reporting to the Senior Manager, Data & Analytics, this role is responsible for supporting the management of data and any associated databases for use across the organization; and transforming data into business insights and generating various types of reports for informed-decision making by internal users (including Management) and external users (including automobile insurance industry Member companies and Regulatory bodies).
 This role requires solid analytical skills and strong attention to detail, the ability to multitask in a complex, fast-paced environment, thrive in producing work of a high quality in a timely manner.

 Duties and Responsibilities:


 Develop monthly/quarterly/ad-hoc dashboards and reports for internal and external use;
 Transform data from vetted sources and generate data visualizations to illustrate trends to empower management with data-driven decision making capabilities;
 Apply industry knowledge and strategic thinking, generate business insights for management and internal teams to address key business challenges;
 Support the ongoing operation of information classification system and related applications, including data needs of other departments;
 Support the data quality assurance analyses and report on such as well as recommendation for fixes;
 Assist in preparation, review, and distribution of monthly operational reporting to internal and external stakeholders;
 Assist the implementation and ongoing operation of the Underwriting Information Plan (UIP), including communication with FA Member Companies, Committee Members and Service Providers;
 Assist in the preparation of presentation materials for various committees as needed; and
 Develop, manage, and maintain process flow documentation







Qualifications: 


University degree in computer science, data engineering, actuarial science or equivalent with a focus on data management;
 Minimum 1 year business analysis experience within the Financial Services industry - Canadian Property & Casualty Insurance Industry with large scale automobile insurance data analysis/management experience is an asset;
 Advanced knowledge of Microsoft Office (Excel, Access, Word, PowerPoint), database management software (SQL, SAS or R);
 Experience in Tableau or related business intelligence platform;
 Motivated self-starter capable of working independently as well as in a team environment;
 Intellectually curious who thrives on uncovering insights hidden in data and translate findings into business interpretations; and
 Excellent time management and organizational skills and ability to work under tight deadlines;


 Assets:



 Experience in all aspects of data analytics, including mining, generation, and visualization;
 Ability to be flexible, learn quickly and adapt to changes in technology and techniques;
 Ability to collaborate across departments through clear and effective written and verbal communication skills; and
 Strong interpersonal skills and a positive, team-oriented attitude 






