 Frima, a proudly Quebec-based company, has been developing video games on various platforms in collaboration with the industry's biggest players since 2003. Join a high-performance team of professionals whose ambition is to always excel with its partners and to offer productions of a quality worthy of the greatest game producers in the industry.
 At Frima, we cultivate bold creativity! We are proud to have been named one of the best video game employers in Canada in 2021 by GamesIndustry.biz!
 As a Data Analyst, you are responsible to analyze and communicate the data generated by the various free-to-play games through tools and dashboards, as well as to determine trends that result in actionable insights. You are involved both at the studio level as a resource person for data analysis tools, as well as in projects to support the design team.
 What will fill your days:
 Studio-wide

 Help build the standards and best practices for tracking, reporting and analysis of various initiatives in our projects’ live operations;
 Identify the tools that should be used to analyze and synthesize data and ensure that data points are implemented and available to the team;
 Maintain and constantly improve tools, bring new ideas and use best practices to set industry standards.

 Project based

 Analyze Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) and provide insights (such as payment yields and monetization flows) that support the decision-making by the projects’ leaders;
 Produce regular custom reports on key game metrics;
 Design, develop, and maintain reports, visualizations, and dashboards that include KPIs and metrics for the internal team and executive team;
 Identify and develop new metrics to help determine which game features are most popular, identify game imbalances and optimal monetization strategies, etc;
 Analyze data to better understand, model, predict, segment, retain and monetize players;
 Create models to predict key metrics and optimize game retention and monetization;
 Collaborate with stakeholders and expertise directors to obtain and document reporting and analytics requirements that can assist them;
 Work with multi-disciplinary project teams to ensure that the implementation of recommendations in the game will meet requirements;
 Act as a resource person for data access and analysis;
 Write complex sets of SQL queries and Python scripts to extract and analyze large multidimensional datasets using statistical modeling and visualization tools (Tableau, Power BI, QuickSight, Grafana, etc.);
 Develop a deep understanding of user behavior through qualitative and quantitative research;
 Continuously improve or review KPIs to ensure they are meaningful and practical in daily work.

 Your profile looks like this:

 Bachelor's degree in mathematics, statistics, data science or other discipline combined with equivalent work experience;
 Minimum of 3 to 6 years experience in a similar role in developing reports, visualizations, and dashboards using Tableau or other data visualization tools;
 Experience in performing quantitative analysis, statistical modeling and applied statistics, providing recommendations to stakeholders, ideally in the video game industry;
 Experience in data extraction and manipulation;
 Thorough knowledge of logical database design, relational databases and data warehouse principles;
 Excellent SQL skills or other query languages;
 Strong knowledge of Excel and/or statistical software packages;
 Knowledge of Python or other programming languages;
 Bilingualism.

 These skills define you well:

 Passion for data and for video games;
 Strong communication and outreach skills;
 Strong analytical skills;
 Ability to work individually on a project or in a team environment;
 Leadership in the development of new working methods;
 Solution orientated;
 Organization, rigor and team listening.

 At Frima, we take care of our people:

 Work environment recognized by GamesIndustry.biz as one of the best places to work in Canada;
 All the flexibility of a hybrid work mode (work from home and in person);
 Flexible vacation policy with the possibility of having up to 7 weeks annually;
 Wide range of benefits (complete group insurance, telemedicine, flexible group savings, sick days, personal days, flexible schedule, employee and family assistance program)
 Mobility program (monthly RTC pass, parking allowance, Communauto subscription, indoor bike parking);
 Frima Health (allowance for the purchase of ergonomic equipment, chair massages, fresh fruit and snacks, on-site gym, sports activities);
 Unique atmosphere (beautiful work environment, access to a terrace, numerous social activities, lively and vibrant neighborhood).

